    "id": "n_root",
    "text": "Weekend trip 🎒",
    "note": "A weekend away for **two**, first weekend of May.\n\nEvery branch below is one node with a description — the kind of half-plan that otherwise ends up scattered across five different notes.",
    "collapsed": false,
    "children": [
      {
        "id": "n_002",
        "text": "Getting there 🚆",
        "note": "| Option | Time | Price |\n|---|---|---|\n| Train | 4 h | 29 |\n| Night bus | 6 h | 19 |\n| Flight | 1 h | 60+ |\n\nThe train wins: city centre to city centre, no airport transfer.",
        "collapsed": false,
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "n_003",
            "text": "Book the train early",
            "note": "Tickets open **90 days** ahead and the cheap fare sells out first.",
            "collapsed": false,
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "n_004",
            "text": "Tram from the station",
            "note": "",
            "collapsed": false,
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "n_005",
        "text": "Where to stay 🛏",
        "note": "Anywhere inside the tram ring works — the place is small enough to walk.",
        "collapsed": false,
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "n_006",
            "text": "Old town",
            "note": "Everything within reach, but noisy on Saturday night.",
            "collapsed": false,
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "n_007",
            "text": "By the river",
            "note": "Quieter, full of cafés, ten minutes by tram.",
            "collapsed": false,
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "n_008",
        "text": "What to see 🏰",
        "note": "",
        "collapsed": false,
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "n_009",
            "text": "The old bridge at sunrise",
            "note": "> Go before 7 a.m. — by nine it is shoulder to shoulder.\n\nThe light from the _east_ end is the good one.",
            "collapsed": false,
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "n_010",
            "text": "The castle",
            "note": "",
            "collapsed": false,
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "n_011",
            "text": "Hilltop lookout",
            "note": "",
            "collapsed": false,
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "n_012",
        "text": "Food & drink 🍽",
        "note": "Two rules: eat where the menu is not translated into five languages, and always ask before they pour the water.",
        "collapsed": false,
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "n_013",
            "text": "The one local dish",
            "note": "",
            "collapsed": false,
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "n_014",
            "text": "Beer garden by the river",
            "note": "Best view in town, plastic cups, cash only.",
            "collapsed": false,
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "n_015",
        "text": "Before you go ✅",
        "note": "1. Book the train\n2. Download an offline map\n3. Get some cash — many places take **no cards**\n4. Check the forecast (below)",
        "collapsed": false,
        "children": [
          {
            "id": "n_016",
            "text": "What to pack",
            "note": "| Day | Evening |\n|---|---|\n| Walking shoes | One warm layer |\n| Water bottle | Something smarter |\n| Sunglasses | Umbrella |",
            "collapsed": false,
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "id": "n_017",
            "text": "Weather in May",
            "note": "Around **18 °C**, and it _will_ rain at least once. Map and forecast: [OpenStreetMap](https://www.openstreetmap.org/).",
            "collapsed": false,
            "children": []
          }
        ]
